  "text": "Induction ofContact Sensitivity. Contact sensitivity was induced by injection of 2,4-dinitro benzene sulfonic acid (DNBS; Eastman Kodak, Rochester, NY)-modified or FITC-modified CB1 cells pretreated or not with GM-CSF (200 ng/ml) . CB1 cells were derivatized with either 200 Ftg/ml of FITC (Sigma Chemical Co .) or with 1 mg/ml DNBS for 30 min at 37°C as described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and inoculated subcutaneously into the dorsal skin of DBA/2 mice. Each mouse received 10\"-105 cells suspended in HBSS in a final vol of 250 AL Recipient mice and nonsensitized controls were ear challenged 5 d later with either 25 pg FITC or 15 hg of 2,4-dinitro-1-fluorobenzene (DNFA Sigma Chemical Co .) on each side of both ears. Mice sensitized epicutaneously were painted with 150 Ag DNFB or 2 mg FITC on the shaved abdomen, as described [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Ear thickness was measured with an engineer's micrometer.",
